Program: Last Word
Title: Christopher Hitchens, Lynn Margulis, George Whitman and Jerry Robinson
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b0184w5r
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 18 Dec 2011
John Wilson on: Christopher Hitchens, a giant of modern political journalism, who targeted tyranny, corruption and religion in print. Microbiologist Lynn Margulis, whose theories about evolution brought about new understanding of cellular development. George Whitman, owner of the world famous Shakespeare and co. bookshop in Paris. And Jerry Robinson, the comic strip artist who created the character of Batman's faithful sidekick Robin and his arch villain The Joker. Show less